      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Nope.  That&#39;s not what heap pollution is.  &quot;Heap pollution occurs when a variable of a parameterized type refers to an object that is not of that parameterized type.&quot; Ref: <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/generics/nonReifiableVarargsType.html#heap_pollution\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/generics/&hellip;</a>"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
