      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@VasiliyVlasov This issue is only relevant for parameterized varargs. If you try to do the same thing with non-typed arrays the runtime will prevent you from inserting the wrong type into the array. The compiler is warning you that the runtime will be unable to prevent incorrect behavior because the parameter type is unknown at runtime (by contrast, arrays <i>do</i> know the type of their non-generic elements at runtime)."
    }, {
